WEBVTT

00:02.169 --> 00:04.160
[m1

00:04.463 --> 00:05.919
[SIREN WAILING]

00:09.051 --> 00:10.882
[DOOR OPENS THEN CLOSES]

00:14.890 --> 00:17.677
KOZLOV:
I do apologize for keeping you waiting.

00:18.310 --> 00:21.518
-Mikhail Kozlov.
-Are you the embassy intelligence Chief?

00:21.730 --> 00:26.224
We are not here to discuss
my curriculum vitae, Agent Keen.

00:26.610 --> 00:29.477
Only to ascertain why you're here
and what you hope to accomplish...

00:29.655 --> 00:32.021
...now that the FBI
has surrounded the embassy.

00:32.241 --> 00:36.405
I am not here to speak to
a pawn without adequate clearance.

00:36.828 --> 00:41.288
Nor are we here to harbor foreign agents
of the FBI, Agent Keen.

00:46.964 --> 00:48.875
My name is Masha Rostova.

00:49.091 --> 00:53.175
I am a deep cover operative for
the Federalnaya Sluzhba Bezopasnosti.

00:53.554 --> 00:57.513
l have successfully completed my
mission and am hereby seeking asylum.

00:57.683 --> 00:59.844
I'd appreciate
an immediate, private audience...

01:00.018 --> 01:02.634
...with your chief intelligence officer.

01:02.813 --> 01:04.644
[SPEAKS IN RUSSIAN]

01:06.108 --> 01:09.771
I need to speak to whoever's in command
of security, and I need to do it now.

01:09.987 --> 01:11.818
-Do you understand?
SAMAR: Ressler.

01:15.158 --> 01:18.025
-Just got off the line with Reven Wright.
-We get the go-ahead?

01:18.203 --> 01:20.910
The State Department requested
the Russians bring her out.

01:21.081 --> 01:24.744
Requested? Nobody would be making
a request if it was Bin Laden in there.

01:24.918 --> 01:27.295
On U.S. soil?
We'd be blasting our way in there.

01:27.462 --> 01:30.204
The Russian embassy isn't U.S. soil.
That fence is a border.

01:30.382 --> 01:33.795
Crossing it is tantamount to
armed invasion. It's literally an act of war.

01:33.969 --> 01:36.176
I know. But look around.

01:36.346 --> 01:38.177
The war's already started.

01:38.682 --> 01:40.673
[m1

01:41.476 --> 01:43.467
[CAMERA BEEPS]

01:50.277 --> 01:52.017
RASKOVITCH:
Agent Keen.

01:54.615 --> 01:56.856
Or do you prefer Rostova?

02:07.210 --> 02:08.245
[SHOWER RUNNING]

02:08.420 --> 02:09.409
[MAN & WOMAN LAUGHING]

02:09.588 --> 02:11.374
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

02:11.548 --> 02:13.504
MAN: Ugh.
WOMAN: Connie, leave it!

02:13.675 --> 02:16.337
MAN:
Patience, go/ubushka. Duty calls.

02:16.511 --> 02:17.671
[CHIMES]

02:22.893 --> 02:26.260
Oh, Connie.
What a delightful nod to tradition.

02:26.438 --> 02:30.522
I can't tell you how nostalgic it is
to see a Russian bureaucrat...

02:30.692 --> 02:35.106
...demonstrating such a time-honored
absence of work ethic.

02:35.489 --> 02:37.400
WOMAN:
Connie? ls someone here?

02:37.574 --> 02:40.862
No, darling. Keep the shower running.
I'll be right in.

02:41.036 --> 02:42.116
I bought us a toy.

02:43.330 --> 02:44.570
Mm....

02:44.748 --> 02:45.783
[GIGGLES]

02:45.957 --> 02:50.246
She's much prettier than she looks
sitting behind the news anchor desk.

02:50.462 --> 02:53.169
-Get out.
-She's married to a ranking member...

02:53.382 --> 02:55.418
...of the Senate Foreign
Relations Committee.

02:55.592 --> 03:01.462
Only fair, I suppose, given the black book
military aid he's allocated to Crimea.

03:01.640 --> 03:04.598
Reciprocity's a bitch. Right, Connie?

03:04.768 --> 03:08.386
Screw the bear, the bear screws back.
Batteries not included.

03:10.232 --> 03:12.188
By all means, do call in the troops.

03:12.359 --> 03:15.567
What with your government's implication
in the OREA bombing...

03:15.779 --> 03:18.020
...and assassinations
of a sitting senator...

03:18.198 --> 03:20.735
...and the attorney general
of the United States...

03:20.909 --> 03:23.821
...how much harm could
a weekly game of water-wiggle...

03:23.995 --> 03:27.237
...between their ambassador
and a senator's wife cause?

03:27.416 --> 03:30.032
Barely a blip in the news cycle.

03:30.377 --> 03:34.791
Though I doubt the Kremlin
will be nearly as jejune as I am.

03:36.341 --> 03:38.423
-What do you want?
-That's the spirit, Connie.

03:38.593 --> 03:40.675
Service with a smile.

03:41.263 --> 03:45.506
The reason your underlings are
so rudely interrupting your weekly tryst...

03:45.726 --> 03:49.810
...is because Elizabeth Keen
turned herself into your embassy...

03:49.980 --> 03:54.849
...and has identified herself
as a deep-cover FSB agent in distress.

03:55.026 --> 03:57.062
Heh. That's absurd.

03:57.237 --> 03:59.148
RAYMOND:
Ha-ha-ha. Yes, quite.

03:59.322 --> 04:02.940
Nevertheless, she's currently
demanding diplomatic immunity.

04:03.160 --> 04:07.529
And I want real-time reports
of everything.

04:08.165 --> 04:11.703
Everything that occurs
inside that building.

04:11.877 --> 04:15.369
Especially the names
of every drone in the decision loop...

04:15.714 --> 04:18.171
...between here and Moscow.

04:18.675 --> 04:21.462
That won't present a problem,
will it, Connie?

04:22.095 --> 04:23.676
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

04:24.639 --> 04:26.721
Duty calls, comrade.

04:27.893 --> 04:30.475
-Who are you?
-Alexander Raskovitch.

04:30.645 --> 04:33.728
FSB chief intelligence agent
for Washington, DC...

04:33.940 --> 04:38.149
...which makes me senior intelligent
agent for the entire Western hemisphere.

04:38.361 --> 04:42.400
I am intimately acquainted with
every single Russian intelligent asset...

04:42.574 --> 04:46.658
...in North and South America,
active and inactive.

04:46.828 --> 04:49.240
And you, dear, are not one of them.

04:49.414 --> 04:52.497
Which begs a question:
Why are you masquerading as such...

04:52.667 --> 04:55.625
...when you and I both know
you are no such thing?

04:55.796 --> 04:57.377
I came here to protect myself.

04:57.589 --> 05:00.331
To get your help
because our interests are aligned.

05:00.550 --> 05:03.667
Your country and l have been blamed
for crimes we did not commit.

05:03.887 --> 05:09.132
It was committed by a global consortium
known in some quarters as the Cabal.

05:10.393 --> 05:11.644
What are their objectives?

05:11.853 --> 05:15.266
To reignite the Cold War
between Russia and the United States.

05:15.649 --> 05:18.482
-And to what end?
-I will tell you everything that I know...

05:18.652 --> 05:24.443
...after I've been guaranteed,
in writing, diplomatic immunity.

05:24.866 --> 05:27.243
How do I know
that you're not working for the Cabal?

05:27.452 --> 05:30.034
How do I know that
you're not here posing as a victim...

05:30.205 --> 05:32.617
...to gain safe passage
away from the FBI?

05:33.291 --> 05:35.407
The Russian assassin...

05:35.627 --> 05:37.834
...the one known as Karakurt....

05:40.715 --> 05:42.296
Never heard of him.

05:44.135 --> 05:45.750
He's been turned.

05:45.971 --> 05:47.552
The Cabal framed me.

05:47.722 --> 05:51.089
Who better than the daughter
of a KGB agent.

05:51.601 --> 05:53.466
Mm. Katarina Rostova.

05:53.645 --> 05:56.637
A KGB agent was turned,
but it wasn't me.

05:56.857 --> 05:58.688
It was Karakurt. He's gone.

05:58.900 --> 06:01.607
Check. And when you've confirmed
he's missing...

06:01.820 --> 06:03.856
...draw up my immunity agreement.

06:05.073 --> 06:07.064
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

06:07.284 --> 06:09.115
-Did we get the breach order?
-Negative.

06:09.286 --> 06:12.449
Russians are denying the State's
request. They're not turning her in.

06:12.622 --> 06:16.456
-ls the White House involved?
-We've been ordered to stand down.

06:16.835 --> 06:19.998
-They're harboring a terrorist.
-The State Department has been clear.

06:20.171 --> 06:22.628
They want this handled diplomatically.

06:24.009 --> 06:26.216
Hold your positions.

06:35.103 --> 06:37.264
My superiors
are willing to hear you out.

06:37.480 --> 06:40.187
If they believe you,
they will do what they can to help.

06:40.358 --> 06:41.734
But not here.

06:41.985 --> 06:45.477
You're being transferred
to Moscow for debriefing.

06:45.655 --> 06:48.237
Don't you see that's playing
into the Cabal's narrative?

06:48.450 --> 06:51.533
Minute I leave, my government
will interpret that as a defection.

06:51.703 --> 06:54.285
l have delivered our decision.

06:54.623 --> 06:56.284
Choose, Agent Keen.

06:56.458 --> 07:01.623
Moscow, or you can take your chances
with your compatriots outside.

07:06.134 --> 07:08.125
[CONNIE SPEAKING IN RUSSIAN]

07:10.055 --> 07:11.261
[SHOUTING IN RUSSIAN]

07:11.765 --> 07:14.882
-Where's my wedding ring?
-Bedside table.

07:15.060 --> 07:17.392
Behind the Ben Wa balls.

07:24.611 --> 07:26.943
-You.
-Me?

07:28.448 --> 07:33.863
And I was so riveted by her interview with
those identical triplets from Milwaukee.

07:34.037 --> 07:35.447
[SPEAKS IN RUSSIAN]

07:35.622 --> 07:38.989
-Agent Keen is leaving the embassy.
-She's been arrested?

07:39.209 --> 07:41.916
The Kremlin has ordered
her transfer to Moscow.

07:42.128 --> 07:43.117
Who in the Kremlin?

07:43.296 --> 07:47.585
It was authorized by
the Federal Tariff Service, of all things.

07:48.218 --> 07:49.708
Vitsin.

07:49.886 --> 07:51.877
[m1

08:07.153 --> 08:08.188
[SPEAKS IN RUSSIAN]

08:10.156 --> 08:12.989
-The package is in transit.
-Excellent.

08:13.159 --> 08:14.865
See Agent Keen to the airport.

08:15.036 --> 08:17.573
Our people on the plane
will take it from there.

08:23.420 --> 08:25.411
[m1

08:28.466 --> 08:30.457
[ENGINE STARTS]

08:31.302 --> 08:33.293
[GATE BEEPS]

08:50.280 --> 08:51.861
SAMAR:
Ressler.

08:52.157 --> 08:53.146
Ressler, don't.

08:53.450 --> 08:56.908
Gonna tell me diplomatic vehicles have
the same protection as the embassy?

08:57.078 --> 08:59.069
You know they do.
As long as she's inside...

08:59.289 --> 09:01.371
...she's on Russian soil.
You can't touch her.

09:01.541 --> 09:04.499
[IN RUSSIAN]
He opens that door, shoot him.

09:07.005 --> 09:08.745
I can't let her go.

09:15.722 --> 09:16.802
SAMAR:
Ressler.

09:17.015 --> 09:19.973
I know you're angry, so am I.
But how we feel is not important.

09:20.393 --> 09:24.102
Taking her into custody is.
We are doing everything we can.

09:24.314 --> 09:28.148
-Are we? Really?
-Within the law, yes. Really.

09:28.401 --> 09:30.392
[J‘J‘J‘]

09:52.967 --> 09:54.468
MAN 1 [OVER RADIO]:
On the move.

09:57.263 --> 10:00.255
MAN 2 [OVER RADIO]: Copy that,
Dispatch. 81, we are on the move.

10:00.433 --> 10:02.469
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

10:02.644 --> 10:03.929
-Ressler.
RAYMOND: Dona/d.

10:04.270 --> 10:06.431
You cannot let Agent Keen
leave the embassy.

10:06.606 --> 10:09.564
You want a favor? How about you
come down and ask in person?

10:09.776 --> 10:11.357
Her life depends on it.

10:11.569 --> 10:14.060
I'd be more inclined to help
if I had you in cuffs.

10:14.280 --> 10:16.487
You cannot let her leave.

10:16.658 --> 10:18.944
You're preaching to the choir,
she's already gone.

10:20.078 --> 10:23.411
I received direct confirmation
from the Russian ambassador...

10:23.581 --> 10:27.995
...that Agent Keen's transfer was
authorized by a high-level apparatchik...

10:28.169 --> 10:32.378
...in the Federal Tariff Service.
A man named Vladimir Vitsin.

10:32.590 --> 10:33.796
-Vitsin.
-Yes.

10:33.967 --> 10:35.798
The same man
who signed the papen/vork...

10:35.969 --> 10:39.461
...facilitating Karakurt's entry
into the United States.

10:39.681 --> 10:41.262
He's an operative for the Cabal.

10:41.474 --> 10:43.886
Any move he makes
is in service to their agenda.

10:47.355 --> 10:49.471
The second She gets on that plane--

10:49.691 --> 10:50.726
She's dead.

10:51.442 --> 10:53.899
You need to stop that convoy.

10:57.991 --> 10:59.822
[VEHICLE APPROACHING]

11:01.619 --> 11:03.234
[TIRES SCREECHING]

11:03.413 --> 11:04.994
[w]

11:06.457 --> 11:08.072
[HORN HONKING]

11:18.094 --> 11:19.504
Shoot him, damn it. Shoot him!

11:20.805 --> 11:22.011
[TIRES SCREECHING]

11:23.516 --> 11:25.222
[SHOUTS IN RUSSIAN]

11:28.354 --> 11:29.560
[MAN GRUNTS]

11:36.821 --> 11:37.856
[GUNSHOT]

11:38.031 --> 11:39.567
CHAUFFEUR:
Kill her!

12:06.851 --> 12:08.227
[GUNSHOTS]

12:28.915 --> 12:30.280
RESSLER:
Keen!

12:31.960 --> 12:33.666
[w]

12:34.545 --> 12:36.285
[BOTH GRUNTING]

12:43.554 --> 12:46.011
[PANTING]

12:54.440 --> 12:56.431
[w]

12:57.860 --> 12:59.236
[PHONE BEEPS]

13:06.452 --> 13:08.443
[LINE RINGING]

13:10.164 --> 13:11.825
[CHIME OVER PHONE]

13:17.880 --> 13:20.838
1425 Peabody.

13:28.683 --> 13:31.425
It's the best I could do.
Full pension and benefits.

13:31.602 --> 13:32.978
If I resign.

13:33.146 --> 13:34.727
Yes, effective immediately.

13:34.939 --> 13:37.681
In return, all charges against you
will be dropped.

13:37.859 --> 13:39.645
Agent Keen. Have you found her?

13:39.861 --> 13:42.022
-I can't discuss--
-Have you found Karakurt?

13:42.447 --> 13:43.857
He's the terrorist, not her.

13:44.073 --> 13:46.234
I took your case
as far as the White House.

13:46.409 --> 13:50.368
I talked to Laurel Hitchin. She's a friend.
She had to pull strings to get this deal.

13:50.538 --> 13:53.075
I appreciate what you've done, Reven.
I do.

13:53.249 --> 13:56.992
These are serious charges, Harold.
You could go to jail.

13:57.170 --> 14:01.254
Take the deal. For you and for Charlene.
Take it and move on.

14:02.216 --> 14:04.798
If you accept the terms,
they'll drop the investigation.

14:05.011 --> 14:07.673
If you refuse to play ball,
pending the outcome...

14:07.847 --> 14:10.634
...you'll be reassigned.
Paper-pushing at the CJIS.

14:10.808 --> 14:13.515
Cubicle. Potted plant.
A dead end, Harold.

14:13.686 --> 14:15.426
You're better than that.

14:15.646 --> 14:17.182
Yes, I am.

14:19.484 --> 14:23.397
-You really want to do this?
-NO. What I want to do is help.

14:25.323 --> 14:29.191
MAN: You think I'm stupid, Carly?
You think I don't know what's going on?

14:29.369 --> 14:31.030
WOMAN:
There's nothing going on.

14:32.413 --> 14:34.369
What are you looking at, Old man?

14:37.085 --> 14:38.871
[DOOR BELLS JINGLE]

14:39.045 --> 14:40.125
[SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY]

14:51.557 --> 14:54.674
-You all right?
-NO, I am not all right.

14:55.603 --> 14:57.309
Ressler tried to kill me.

14:57.855 --> 15:00.767
Seeking asylum with the Russians
was a dangerous decision.

15:00.942 --> 15:02.773
l was out of options.

15:02.944 --> 15:05.185
At least I would have been secure
in Moscow.

15:05.405 --> 15:08.192
If by "secure," you mean dead,
then, yes, absolutely.

15:08.616 --> 15:12.234
Ressler wasn't trying to kill you,
he was trying to save you.

15:12.578 --> 15:15.069
The convoy was compromised.

15:17.417 --> 15:19.749
If you want, we got a few specials.

15:19.919 --> 15:23.127
The best item on the menu
is the pecan pie. Right, Chui?

15:23.339 --> 15:26.331
-Family recipe.
-|'|| just have coffee. Thanks.

15:29.262 --> 15:31.048
You know him? We're safe here?

15:32.640 --> 15:35.052
You threw yourself
in the hands of the Cabal...

15:35.226 --> 15:37.262
...the moment you got on that vehicle.

15:37.562 --> 15:42.181
Only question was whether they'd kill you
before or after entering Russian airspace.

15:42.483 --> 15:44.474
CARLY:
Ow. Please, you're hurting me.

15:46.028 --> 15:47.438
[CARLY GRUNTS]

15:48.448 --> 15:51.781
You deaf, old man?
I told you to mind your own business.

15:51.993 --> 15:54.575
-Turn around, bitch.
CARLY: Clayton.

15:55.079 --> 15:56.865
[w]

15:58.875 --> 16:01.662
CLAYTON: Oh, here we go.
-Carly.

16:01.878 --> 16:03.834
What the hell?
You looking to get yourself killed?

16:04.005 --> 16:05.245
[CARLY GASPS]

16:10.052 --> 16:13.920
You haven't the slightest clue
how to speak to a woman, have you?

16:15.725 --> 16:19.684
Now, my friend there and I
are having a very important discussion...

16:19.896 --> 16:23.480
...so you just sit tight, enjoy your muffin...

16:23.900 --> 16:29.486
...and if I hear you say anything other
than "please" or "thank you" to Carly...

16:29.655 --> 16:34.274
...l'm gonna drag you into the men's room
and wash your mouth out with soap.

16:35.620 --> 16:38.862
And if that doesn't work,
I'll cut your filthy tongue out...

16:39.040 --> 16:41.247
...with that butter knife.

16:44.712 --> 16:46.794
Is that clear enough for you?

16:56.390 --> 16:59.928
Agent Ressler, what part
of "stand down" don't you understand?

17:00.144 --> 17:03.728
RESSLER: I was ordered to let Keen go,
and I did. I wasn't ordered to let her die.

17:03.898 --> 17:06.184
-The transport was compromised.
-Says who?

17:06.359 --> 17:08.065
-Reddington.
-You Spoke to him?

17:08.236 --> 17:12.445
Yes. He called.
Said that the Cabal had hijacked Keen.

17:12.615 --> 17:15.982
You countermanded a direct order
and attacked a diplomatic transport...

17:16.160 --> 17:19.277
...on the word of one fugitive
in order to save the life of another?

17:19.664 --> 17:23.498
I'm willing to resign from the task force
if the intel Reddington gave us is wrong.

17:23.709 --> 17:25.245
The driver has been hospitalized.

17:25.419 --> 17:28.502
As soon as he can be questioned,
we can confirm Red's information.

17:28.714 --> 17:33.504
Okay, we got a sighting.
Del Rio Diner. 1425 Peabody Street.

17:34.345 --> 17:36.336
[w]

17:36.889 --> 17:38.880
[BREATHING DEEPLY]

17:42.311 --> 17:44.688
Come on. Pull it together.

17:56.492 --> 17:59.199
An N.P.D.C. cruiser
just pulled up out back.

18:04.208 --> 18:05.493
What are you--?

18:13.718 --> 18:15.674
[OFFICERS SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

18:16.929 --> 18:18.635
OFFICER:
Behind the car.

18:18.848 --> 18:21.305
[w]

18:23.811 --> 18:28.601
Ladies and gentlemen,
please remain calm and take your seats.

18:29.942 --> 18:32.058
-Clayton.
LIZ: Now what?

18:33.029 --> 18:36.237
Now? I apologize.

18:40.578 --> 18:43.570
I am terribly sorry
for the inconvenience...

18:43.748 --> 18:46.706
...but it appears
we'll all be taking an extended lunch.

18:46.876 --> 18:51.461
However, if you remain calm
and do exactly as I say...

18:51.631 --> 18:55.670
...I promise you'll leave here
with a rip-roaring story...

18:55.843 --> 18:58.300
...to tell your friends and families.

18:59.347 --> 19:01.383
Bon appétit.

19:01.599 --> 19:02.588
[PHONE RINGING]

19:02.767 --> 19:05.850
Dear, would you mind answering
that phone? NO doubt it's for me.

19:08.689 --> 19:10.680
[EKG BEEPING]

19:13.778 --> 19:16.144
MAN:
Oh, I'm sorry. Did I disturb you?

19:16.322 --> 19:18.278
They said you were sedated.

19:19.408 --> 19:23.196
Well, you know what they say:
Can't keep a good man down.

19:23.746 --> 19:28.035
Unfortunately, it's only a matter of time
before the FBI pays you a visit...

19:28.209 --> 19:30.666
...and we can't have that.

19:30.878 --> 19:36.214
Because you are what is commonly
referred to as a loose end.

19:37.343 --> 19:39.925
Now, you should take heart.

19:40.096 --> 19:43.509
Because if the Russians are furious now,
imagine how irate they'll be...

19:43.683 --> 19:46.299
...when they learn
that there's been another fatality...

19:46.477 --> 19:49.059
...as a result of Agent Ressler's attack
on your convoy.

19:49.980 --> 19:52.642
If it's any consolation,
your heroic devotion...

19:52.817 --> 19:57.481
...to our cause has earned you
my most Sincere respect.

20:02.535 --> 20:04.196
Godspeed, Sir.

20:05.746 --> 20:07.282
Godspeed.

20:08.082 --> 20:10.073
[GRUNTING]

20:12.920 --> 20:14.911
[w]

20:19.885 --> 20:21.876
[EKG BEEPING RAPIDLY]

20:25.641 --> 20:26.972
[CHATTERING]

20:27.143 --> 20:29.134
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

20:34.108 --> 20:36.099
[w]

20:44.326 --> 20:46.863
RESSLER: What do you got?
HRT LEADER: We cut the power.

20:47.037 --> 20:49.619
Commandeered the phone lines.
Both suspects are inside.

20:49.832 --> 20:53.871
-Both suspects?
-Agent Keen and Raymond Reddington.

20:54.462 --> 20:55.872
-Keen?
-We believe so.

20:56.046 --> 20:58.002
He's got the hostages
as human shields.

20:58.174 --> 21:01.587
-Can't get a clear view inside.
-Well, then. Let's find out.

21:01.761 --> 21:03.251
What are you doing?

21:06.265 --> 21:07.596
Hold fire.

21:08.184 --> 21:09.549
RESSLER:
Keen.

21:11.353 --> 21:13.685
-Keen!
-Ah.

21:18.110 --> 21:19.850
Agent Ressler, excellent.

21:20.029 --> 21:23.567
DO you have a pen? Because I'm ready
to dictate a list of my demands.

21:23.783 --> 21:26.445
I owe you, Keen. You saved my life
back at that convoy.

21:26.660 --> 21:28.446
Now let me return the favor.

21:28.662 --> 21:30.493
Come out before this gets bad.

21:30.706 --> 21:33.789
It's already gone bad,
and you're making it worse.

21:33.959 --> 21:37.247
If you wanna repay me, do what he says
before somebody else gets hurt.

21:37.421 --> 21:40.254
That won't happen, and you know it.
The scene's locked down.

21:40.466 --> 21:44.584
There's nowhere to go and you got
zero leverage because I know you.

21:45.429 --> 21:48.592
I know what you're capable of.
You're not gonna hurt these people.

21:48.766 --> 21:51.007
She won't, but I will.

21:51.227 --> 21:53.969
Ready? My demands are as follows:

21:54.146 --> 21:57.684
One, I want the immediate restoration
of power to this building.

21:57.900 --> 22:00.937
Two, an armored vehicle
to transport us...

22:01.153 --> 22:06.273
...safely and unmolested from this door
to a runway of my choosing.

22:06.450 --> 22:09.908
Three, bring me Marvin Gerard.

22:10.287 --> 22:12.403
-You have 90 minutes.
-That's it?

22:12.581 --> 22:15.163
After that,
a hostage dies every half hour.

22:15.334 --> 22:16.915
That's it, Agent Ressler.

22:28.430 --> 22:29.931
RESSLER:
Marvin Gerard.

22:30.099 --> 22:32.010
Graduated magna cum laude
from Harvard...

22:32.184 --> 22:34.891
...where, at the tender age of 31,
he was appointed...

22:35.062 --> 22:38.145
...the third youngest full professor
in the institution's history.

22:38.315 --> 22:40.727
He served as a prosecutor
for three years, New York.

22:40.901 --> 22:44.189
Later, joined his father-in-Iaw's
criminal defense firm as a partner.

22:44.405 --> 22:47.067
He was on the Short list
for the federal bench...

22:47.283 --> 22:49.990
...when his marriage
to the boss's daughter hit the skids.

22:50.160 --> 22:53.778
He serves a year for attempting
to kidnap their son. Gets disbarred.

22:53.956 --> 22:58.120
Currently he's incarcerated for
seven to 10 in the Cumberland FCI.

22:58.335 --> 23:00.667
Although disbarred,
he acts as shadow counsel...

23:00.838 --> 23:05.582
...to some Of the biggest players in the
criminal undenNorld. Politicians, CEOs...

23:05.759 --> 23:07.499
...and one Raymond Reddington.

23:07.803 --> 23:09.168
-Marvin Gerard?
MARVIN: Who are you?

23:09.930 --> 23:11.010
What am I doing here?

23:11.223 --> 23:13.760
I'm Special Agent Samar Navabi.
You been briefed?

23:13.976 --> 23:19.312
Rousted out of bed, cavity searched,
shackled, transported like livestock?

23:19.481 --> 23:21.346
Yes. Briefed? NO.

23:21.525 --> 23:25.143
One of your former clients is holding
17 civilians hostage in that diner.

23:25.738 --> 23:28.104
He's demanded that we bring you here.

23:28.282 --> 23:30.614
-Which one?
-Raymond Reddington.

23:32.077 --> 23:34.238
l have nothing to do with this.

23:34.455 --> 23:37.572
I don't know what he wants from me.
I am not going in there.

23:37.791 --> 23:39.747
Well, you are going in.

23:40.127 --> 23:41.583
If you could please disrobe....

23:41.795 --> 23:44.832
Like hell. Call my lawyer.
Who is your O.I.C.?

23:45.049 --> 23:49.292
That would be me. Gentlemen,
help Mr. Gerard out Of his jumpsuit.

23:51.680 --> 23:54.638
This will never work. If he asks,
I'm gonna have to tell him...

23:54.850 --> 23:56.010
...l'm wearing a wire.

23:56.185 --> 23:58.426
It would be unethical for me
to lie to my client.

23:58.604 --> 24:01.892
Let the record reflect
that I am complying under duress...

24:02.066 --> 24:06.400
...and that my Fourth Amendment right
to privacy is being violated.

24:06.570 --> 24:08.731
As is my right not to be nauseated.

24:09.156 --> 24:11.317
Per Reddington's demands.

24:12.159 --> 24:13.490
Unbelievable.

24:16.747 --> 24:18.658
RAYMOND:
I'll get that, dear.

24:19.249 --> 24:20.955
The first table. Over there.

24:26.799 --> 24:28.960
[COFFEE POURING]

24:29.802 --> 24:31.212
[WHISPERS]
This is not working.

24:32.346 --> 24:34.257
Lizzy, please.

24:34.807 --> 24:38.140
Take a seat.
I'll have Chui bring you a piece of pie.

24:38.310 --> 24:39.686
I promise, you'll thank me.

24:40.020 --> 24:42.261
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
Would you cut it out? A lawyer?

24:42.481 --> 24:44.142
How is that gonna help us with this?

24:44.358 --> 24:48.727
Lawyers find and exploit loopholes.
It's what makes them so loathsome.

24:48.904 --> 24:53.113
And Marvin Gerard
is the most loathsome of them all.

24:53.325 --> 24:54.906
That's what makes him so invaluable.

24:55.077 --> 24:56.066
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

24:56.286 --> 24:58.493
Speak of the devil.

25:01.917 --> 25:05.159
-HeIIO, Marvin.
-My parole hearing is next week.

25:05.421 --> 25:07.207
Christmas came early.

25:13.679 --> 25:15.419
You think this is a gift?

25:15.597 --> 25:20.182
They'll probably tack on five more years
just seeing you breathe in my direction.

25:21.729 --> 25:23.594
-Are you wired?
-Of course I'm wired.

25:23.772 --> 25:24.761
[LAUGHS]

25:24.940 --> 25:28.353
I told them not to bother.
I told you not to bother.

25:28.944 --> 25:31.310
Elizabeth, Marvin Gerard.

25:31.530 --> 25:32.940
-[OVER RADIO] Criminal attorney.
-One down.

25:33.157 --> 25:35.068
Not necessarily in that order.

25:35.242 --> 25:38.109
Finally, I am in the presence
of greatness.

25:38.328 --> 25:41.616
You're the one. You're the one
who made him throw away his freedom.

25:41.790 --> 25:44.497
-Good God, Marv, let it go.
-What? You asked for my advice.

25:44.668 --> 25:49.378
l was simply giving you, as a friend,
a heads-up regarding my plans.

25:49.548 --> 25:53.291
-You were a wonderful attorney.
-And you were a terrible client.

25:54.344 --> 25:55.333
Two.

25:55.512 --> 25:56.501
[STATIC CRACKLING OVER RADIO]

25:56.680 --> 25:57.965
MARVIN:
Not that you're interested...

25:58.140 --> 26:02.634
...but I just got engaged.

26:03.062 --> 26:04.927
Becky Weinberg.

26:05.105 --> 26:06.094
[HIGH-PITCHED SCREECH
OVER RADIO]

26:06.273 --> 26:09.765
That little brunette Becky.
From the old firm. The paralegal.

26:10.736 --> 26:12.567
Oh, my God, you old dog.

26:14.531 --> 26:16.613
-Oh, ha, ha.
-Getting Older by the minute.

26:16.825 --> 26:19.692
You just extended my engagement
about a decade with this stunt.

26:19.870 --> 26:21.610
Now I'm never gonna make parole.

26:21.830 --> 26:25.288
Becky and |--
She's not gonna wait around.

26:25.459 --> 26:27.950
RAYMOND: All right, counselor.
Let's get down to business.

26:28.170 --> 26:32.038
l have a situation that requires
your undivided attention.

26:32.216 --> 26:34.127
NO, it doesn't. Turn yourselves in.

26:34.843 --> 26:37.755
RAYMOND: Marvin, hear me out.
You don't have all the facts.

26:37.930 --> 26:39.215
MARVIN:
NO, but I have eyes.

26:39.389 --> 26:42.005
And I can see that you're in here
and they're out there.

26:42.184 --> 26:44.266
Now you're gonna
start in with me about how...

26:44.478 --> 26:46.890
...with you, there's always
more than meets the eye.

26:47.564 --> 26:49.145
-NO!
-Elizabeth!

26:49.316 --> 26:50.305
[w]

26:50.484 --> 26:52.145
[BOTH GRUNTING]

26:58.200 --> 27:00.486
CHUI: Unh!
-Stop!

27:01.537 --> 27:03.073
That's enough!

27:03.705 --> 27:05.696
[CLAYTON WHEEZING
AND GROANING]

27:24.059 --> 27:26.050
[w]

27:48.125 --> 27:49.114
[CLAYTON WHEEZING]

27:49.293 --> 27:52.035
You broke his ribs.
It sounds like his lung is punctured.

27:52.212 --> 27:53.292
[CLAYTON GROANING]

27:53.463 --> 27:55.840
-You're hurting him.
LIZ: Only way to stop the swelling.

27:56.008 --> 27:58.169
-What do you care?
-I didn't want anybody hurt.

27:58.343 --> 28:00.834
Really? Seemed to me
like you wanted to hurt him bad.

28:01.013 --> 28:04.005
RAYMOND: She didn't have a choice.
What if he'd gotten her gun?

28:04.224 --> 28:06.966
What then? You think we would be
safer if he were armed?

28:07.186 --> 28:08.596
You think you'd be safe?

28:15.777 --> 28:18.644
What is he working on?
A plea agreement?

28:19.364 --> 28:21.980
Why else bring a lawyer in here
other than to cut a deal?

28:22.201 --> 28:24.362
If you think for one second
I'm interested--

28:24.578 --> 28:25.613
There will be no deal.

28:25.787 --> 28:28.403
Then why go to all the trouble
to bring him in here?

28:28.582 --> 28:30.493
It doesn't make any sense.

28:31.043 --> 28:33.580
Marvin Gerard was one
of the most respected...

28:33.754 --> 28:36.461
...defense attorneys
on the eastern seaboard.

28:36.632 --> 28:39.169
Perfect wife, perfectjob. Perfect.

28:39.343 --> 28:42.676
All Of it, save for his son, Timothy.

28:45.682 --> 28:46.933
Quiet boy.

28:48.560 --> 28:51.552
Fell in with some bad eggs, it seems.

28:52.940 --> 28:57.309
Disciplinary issues, troubles at school,
drug abuse.

28:58.195 --> 29:00.857
Timothy was getting a steady
supply of amphetamines...

29:01.073 --> 29:04.156
...from his mother's shrink.
Ritalin, Adderall.

29:04.368 --> 29:07.030
She constantly bullied the boy.

29:07.704 --> 29:10.286
Marvin and his wife separated.
He fought for custody.

29:10.457 --> 29:13.699
Contacted police, social services.

29:13.961 --> 29:18.921
But his wife was the princess in a very
prominent and powerful legal dynasty...

29:19.091 --> 29:20.706
...so no action was ever taken.

29:20.926 --> 29:22.962
Timothy remained in her sole custody.

29:23.387 --> 29:24.547
Her abuse worsened.

29:24.721 --> 29:28.555
Convinced he had no other option,
Marvin kidnapped the boy.

29:29.309 --> 29:33.473
They tracked him down, of course.
Returned the child to his mother.

29:34.940 --> 29:37.977
Marvin was disbarred,
convicted and incarcerated.

29:38.986 --> 29:41.068
And what happened to his son?

29:42.072 --> 29:44.688
A year later, Timothy hung himself.

29:45.617 --> 29:47.528
He was 15.

29:50.539 --> 29:52.120
Snipers in position for cover.

29:52.291 --> 29:55.875
Teams, make simultaneous entries
here and here.

29:56.044 --> 29:59.411
Flash-bangs and smoke.
Secure and contain the scenario.

29:59.589 --> 30:02.752
Count on minimal risk of collateral
damage. We're all set on my mark.

30:02.968 --> 30:06.176
-He can't do that. Can you do that?
-NO. We don't have eyes inside.

30:06.346 --> 30:08.758
Even a minimal risk
of collateral damage is too much.

30:08.932 --> 30:12.470
We wait. Reddington won't hurt anybody
in that building. Keen won't let him.

30:12.686 --> 30:14.551
Same girl who shot
the attorney general?

30:14.730 --> 30:16.766
-That was different.
-She's in over her head.

30:16.940 --> 30:18.316
Probably why they got spotted.

30:18.483 --> 30:22.021
Wasn't her that was spotted. Anonymous
tip came in on Reddington, not Keen.

30:22.195 --> 30:23.605
[w]

30:23.780 --> 30:25.486
Get me that 911 call.

30:38.795 --> 30:40.410
Raymond.

30:42.507 --> 30:44.088
Did you read this?

30:46.261 --> 30:49.219
Yes. It's the voice transcripts
we recovered from the Fulcrum.

30:49.431 --> 30:52.468
NO, I didn't ask if you recognized it,
| asked you if you read it.

30:52.642 --> 30:58.603
Specifically section 39c,
pages 216 and 217, lines 5 through 19.

30:58.774 --> 31:00.310
Here.

31:03.320 --> 31:04.981
RAYMOND:
This can't be right.

31:05.489 --> 31:08.777
God, no. It's all kinds of wrong.

31:10.077 --> 31:13.319
This is a perilously fast run
down a slippery road.

31:13.497 --> 31:16.364
Granted, you'd have to hit
all green lights, but...

31:16.541 --> 31:18.873
...yeah, we could make it work.

31:19.461 --> 31:20.541
CARLY:
He can't breathe.

31:20.754 --> 31:24.372
Somebody help him! NO, not you!
You get away from him!

31:25.175 --> 31:26.506
[SOBBING]

31:29.679 --> 31:32.170
His chest cavity's filling with blood.

31:32.349 --> 31:34.431
His lungs will collapse
if we don't get him...

31:34.601 --> 31:36.592
...medical attention in 20 to 30 minutes.

31:36.770 --> 31:40.183
Fine. He'll be in Agent Ressler's
capable care by then.

31:40.357 --> 31:42.143
-We're leaving.
-Leaving?

31:42.317 --> 31:46.686
Attention, everyone. We're done here,
so if you could all be so kind...

31:46.905 --> 31:49.738
...as to gather up your belongings
and step into the kitchen.

31:49.908 --> 31:52.240
Except you two. You stay right there.
Lucinda?

31:52.953 --> 31:58.994
Chui, be a pal. Wrap up two slices
of that delicious pecan pie.

32:04.589 --> 32:07.672
I spent five years tracking Reddington
and can count on one hand the times...

32:07.843 --> 32:09.299
...we got a credible sighting.

32:09.469 --> 32:10.845
lfound the 911 call.

32:11.096 --> 32:13.087
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

32:13.765 --> 32:14.971
RESSLER:
One second.

32:15.142 --> 32:16.427
RAYMOND:
I’m very disappointed, Donald.

32:16.601 --> 32:18.637
I would've expected you,
of all people...

32:18.854 --> 32:22.187
...would've understood that when
| make a demand, it's just that.

32:22.399 --> 32:23.809
Stalling is not tolerated.

32:24.025 --> 32:26.732
-We're doing the best we can.
-Why isn't the power back on?

32:27.362 --> 32:28.772
Where's my armored vehicle?

32:28.989 --> 32:30.820
-We're working on it.
-Work harder.

32:31.032 --> 32:34.069
If the power isn't back in 60 seconds,
I'll start shooting people.

32:34.244 --> 32:35.700
Your time starts now.

32:39.291 --> 32:41.327
HRT LEADER: Give him the power.
-He's bluffing.

32:41.543 --> 32:44.034
I can't take that chance.
Restore the power.

33:01.605 --> 33:03.095
Counselor.

33:09.154 --> 33:10.314
Oh! Ha, ha.

33:10.614 --> 33:13.822
The least of your many talents,
my friend.

33:15.785 --> 33:17.776
[ELEVATOR WHIRRING]

33:19.039 --> 33:20.745
RAYMOND [ON RECORDING]:
He just looked right at me.

33:20.916 --> 33:22.907
It's him. It's Reddington.

33:24.211 --> 33:26.497
-That's Reddington.
-Called the tip in on himself.

33:26.713 --> 33:29.921
This whole thing, he wanted us to--
Breach! Breach now!

33:35.180 --> 33:36.716
Okay, everyone, let's pack it up.

33:37.098 --> 33:40.386
I'm sorry you have to burn this Operation
on our account, Chui.

33:40.602 --> 33:41.637
It was beautiful.

33:41.853 --> 33:45.345
If only it lasted. They'll be packed
and long gone before the FBI gets here.

33:45.565 --> 33:46.805
This way.

33:48.109 --> 33:49.440
[EXPLOSION,
THEN CARLY YELLS]

33:49.819 --> 33:50.808
MAN 1: Ranger up!
MAN 2: Go!

33:50.987 --> 33:52.978
[MEN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

33:53.657 --> 33:55.238
Kitchen. Kitchen.

33:58.411 --> 34:00.493
MAN 3: All clear.
MAN 4: Clear!

34:01.957 --> 34:04.289
[w]

34:10.465 --> 34:12.626
-They're not here.
-He|l....

34:13.051 --> 34:15.042
[CLATTERING AND WHIRRING]

34:15.220 --> 34:16.835
HRT LEADER:
Get these people out Of here.

34:17.013 --> 34:18.128
MAN 5:
Okay.

34:18.306 --> 34:20.297
[w]

34:30.777 --> 34:33.314
Didn't just disappear.
There's gotta be a way out.

34:33.488 --> 34:36.230
Break down every wall if you have to.

34:36.866 --> 34:37.946
Find them.

34:42.372 --> 34:44.454
This is a bad situation, Red.

34:44.624 --> 34:46.580
They will hunt me
and they will find me.

34:46.793 --> 34:48.875
And when they do,
do you know where I'm going?

34:49.045 --> 34:50.751
-In a hole.
-DO you like Tahiti?

34:50.922 --> 34:53.834
Solitary. Twenty-three hours a day.
There will be no parole...

34:54.217 --> 34:56.128
...and no chance of seeing Becky again.

34:56.344 --> 34:58.426
-That's for sure.
-You're a free man, Marvin.

34:58.638 --> 35:01.971
Instead of facing a notoriously
unpredictable parole board...

35:02.142 --> 35:04.724
...and showering with the boys,
you'll be unwinding...

35:04.894 --> 35:10.184
...on a small banana plantation
l have outside of Papeete.

35:10.358 --> 35:11.814
[RAYMOND LAUGHS]

35:12.110 --> 35:13.145
Becky.

35:16.031 --> 35:17.237
RAYMOND:
Get in the car, Marvin.

35:17.449 --> 35:19.906
Have a mai tai, soak up some sun...

35:20.118 --> 35:22.951
...because I'll be contacting you soon,
and when I do...

35:23.163 --> 35:26.155
...I want this plan Of yours
to be thoroughly mapped out.

35:26.333 --> 35:28.540
We only have one shot at this.

35:29.753 --> 35:31.209
I'll be in touch.

35:31.796 --> 35:36.540
Make sure you have Heia air-dry
your Sheets. You'll sleep like a baby.

35:36.718 --> 35:37.753
LIZ:
This whole thing...

35:37.969 --> 35:41.336
...the diner, it wasn't a hostage situation,
it was a jail break.

35:41.765 --> 35:42.925
Yes.

35:43.099 --> 35:45.351
We won't be able to fight
our way out of this.

35:45.518 --> 35:47.304
We're gonna have to think our way out.

35:47.479 --> 35:49.686
-You really think he can help?
-I do.

35:50.732 --> 35:52.814
Where do we go from here?

35:52.984 --> 35:54.815
[PEOPLE CHATTERING
AND PHONES RINGING]

35:54.986 --> 35:56.522
RESSLER:
The owner's gone...

35:56.863 --> 35:58.444
...the lawyer's gone...

35:59.199 --> 36:00.905
...and Red and Liz are gone.

36:01.076 --> 36:05.866
Why would he go to all this trouble, risk
everything, just to free Marvin Gerard?

36:08.291 --> 36:12.330
Put the word out. They're in the wind,
and we're back to square one.

36:14.881 --> 36:15.961
RAYMOND:
Mm.

36:16.132 --> 36:18.123
[CLASSICAL MUSIC
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

36:18.301 --> 36:21.088
You have no idea
what I've offered Chui...

36:21.304 --> 36:24.137
...to divulge the secret of this recipe.

36:24.766 --> 36:25.846
He won't say...

36:26.059 --> 36:30.098
...but I suspect it has something to do
with how he beats his eggs.

36:30.271 --> 36:33.729
I cannot stop thinking
about that man from the diner.

36:33.942 --> 36:36.854
-I wonder if he uses a whisk.
-His wife...

36:37.112 --> 36:39.478
...the way she looked at me.

36:40.448 --> 36:42.734
NO one's ever looked at me
like that before.

36:43.576 --> 36:45.988
-How do you do it?
-DO what?

36:46.162 --> 36:50.371
How do you deal with people
looking at you that way? The fear?

36:51.459 --> 36:54.701
How do you go on knowing
that people are terrified Of you?

36:57.340 --> 36:59.296
From as early as I can remember...

36:59.467 --> 37:02.675
...I dreamed of someday
being captain of a ship.

37:03.346 --> 37:06.463
To be out there on the ocean
in the middle of the night...

37:06.641 --> 37:09.257
...navigating by the stars.

37:11.020 --> 37:15.229
| always thought it would be
the greatest life on earth.

37:17.110 --> 37:18.896
The people you're talking about...

37:20.905 --> 37:23.817
...the ones who think they know you...

37:24.784 --> 37:29.118
...they really don't know
anything about you at all.

37:32.709 --> 37:35.621
I've never told anyone that before.

37:36.337 --> 37:38.328
[LAUGHS]

37:38.590 --> 37:40.546
About a life at sea.

37:40.717 --> 37:44.460
Why didn't you do it?
You went into Naval Intelligence instead.

37:45.889 --> 37:49.177
It was the Cold War.
There were spies to run.

37:49.350 --> 37:53.013
The Cabal, they blamed you
for something you hadn't done.

37:53.438 --> 37:58.273
Sailors have been navigating by the stars
for thousands of years.

37:59.360 --> 38:02.693
Odysseus spent a decade at war...

38:02.906 --> 38:06.273
...but his biggest battle
was finding his way home.

38:10.580 --> 38:13.196
I think you would've made
a terrific captain.

38:13.374 --> 38:14.363
